<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="103" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="103">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="103">
The type locality of 
<taxonomicName authority="C.D.Specht" authorityName="Skornick." authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Leong-Škorničková &amp; Böhmová &amp; Tr ần" baseAuthorityYear="2022" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Costaceae" genus="Cheilocostus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cheilocostus tonkinensis" order="Zingiberales" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tonkinensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">Cheilocostus tonkinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is in northern Vietnam, Mount Ba 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Vì">Vi</normalizedToken>
. In the protologue, 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1080/00378941.1902.10830936" author="Gagnepain, F" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin de la Societe Botanique de France" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" pagination="247 - 269" refId="B2" refString="Gagnepain, F, 1902. [publ. 1903] Zingiberacees Nouvelles de L'herbier du Museum (1). Bulletin de la Societe Botanique de France 49 (5): 247 - 269, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1080/00378941.1902.10830936" title="[publ. 1903] Zingiberacees Nouvelles de L'herbier du Museum (1)." url="https://doi.org/10.1080/00378941.1902.10830936" volume="49" year="1902">Gagnepain (1902)</bibRefCitation>
refers to two collections made by Balansa from this locality. There are four sheets at P: a single sheet of 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">Balansa s.n.</emphasis>
, collected on 24 July 1886 [P00686610 - inflorescences &amp; flower] and three sheets of 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">Balansa 4206</emphasis>
collected in October 1887 [P02198384 - leafy shoot &amp; single fruit; P02198381-inflorescence only; P02198385-leafy shoot only]. Both of these collections predate the protologue and are annotated in 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Gagnepain’s">Gagnepain's</normalizedToken>
hand as published in Bull. Bot Soc. France 49: 248. All four sheets have to be considered as syntypes and, therefore, the lectotypification is needed. Unfortunately, none of the specimens consists of both leafy shoot and an inflorescence. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">Balansa s.n.</emphasis>
[P00686610] with inflorescence and a flower, accompanied by a pencil drawing, is selected here as the lectotype.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="103">
It is challenging to distinguish Asian radically flowering 
<taxonomicName authority="C.D.Specht" authorityName="C.D.Specht" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Costaceae" genus="Cheilocostus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Zingiberales" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Costaceae</taxonomicName>
in herbarium material as the flowers do not preserve well. Based on our observations of living flowering material and photographic records with location data, 
<taxonomicName authority="C.D.Specht" authorityName="Skornick." authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Leong-Škorničková &amp; Böhmová &amp; Tr ần" baseAuthorityYear="2022" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Costaceae" genus="Cheilocostus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cheilocostus tonkinensis" order="Zingiberales" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tonkinensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">Cheilocostus tonkinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, so far, occurs in S. China, northern and central Vietnam and northern Laos, but may possibly extend to Thailand.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
